{"questionId":"22263371","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"0\"><p>Calculate</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p>the size of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"2\"><p>the area of triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BAD</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"0\"><p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>use of scalar product formula to find angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>∙</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>use of cosine rule to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1417</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92405</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If the direction of one of the vectors is reversed, leading to an obtuse angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>124</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>858</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math> between the vectors, then award <em><strong>M1A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>an attempt at using vector product&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>or equivalent</p>\n<p>attempt to apply formula (e.g. one correct component)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">i</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">j</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">k</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02493</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>101</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>use of formula for the area of a triangle<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>area<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1417</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for the lengths <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AD</mi></math> and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for the angle.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p></div>","meta":{"questionId":"22263371","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the size of BA^D. the area of triangle BAD.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Vector definitions","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar and vector products"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}